The paper focuses on developing a method for robots to better understand tactile properties of objects through visual and physical interaction data. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since the proposed method involves using visual data. The use of deep neural networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also touches on human-robot interaction, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
